    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nInconsistent CursorLineFold hl in 'foldcolumn' vs 'statuscolumn' on \"below\" virt lines.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Run `nvim --clean`\n2. Source the following Lua file:\n```lua\nvim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(0, 0, -1, true, { 'foo', 'bar', 'baz' })\nlocal ns = vim.api.nvim_create_namespace('test')\nvim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(0, ns, 1, 0, { virt_lines = { { { 'VIRT_LINE' } } } })\nvim.o.foldcolumn = '1'\nvim.o.cursorline = true\nvim.cmd('highlight CursorLineFold guibg=Red')\n```\n3. Move cursor to line 2, notice that the fold column on the virtual line isn't highlighted as red.\n4. Move cursor to line 3, notice that the fold column on the virtual line is highlighted as red.\n5. Run `:set statuscolumn=%C`\n6. Move cursor to line 2, notice that the fold column on the virtual line is highlighted as red.\n7. Move cursor to line 3, notice that the fold column on the virtual line isn't highlighted as red.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe behavior of 'foldcolumn' and 'statuscolumn' `%C` field should be consistent.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.13.0-dev-687+gd72e91a0b6\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\n0.47.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
